'''Brad Byers''' (born October 8, 1959)<ref name=agt>{{cite AV media|people=Brad Byers|year=2013|title=Brad Byers - Performer Lays on Bed of Nails While an ATV Runs Over Him - America's Got Talent 2013|trans-title=|medium=|language=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Af1t3ov_ugM|accessdate=February 16, 2014|archiveurl=|archivedate=|format=|time=|location=|publisher=[[America's Got Talent]]|id=|isbn=|oclc=|quote=|ref=}}</ref> is an American entertainer known for his extreme performances, including [[sword swallowing]], lying on [[Bed of nails|beds of nails]] and inserting various [[tool]]s into his [[nasal cavity]]. For the latter he is also referred to as a “Human [[toolbox]]”. He holds several World Records. His brother Rod assists him in some performances.<ref name=agt/>
== Biography == Brad Byers was born and raised in [[Moscow, Idaho]]. According to the biography given on the official site, he joined a traveling circus to become a juggler shortly after graduating from high school. Two years later he left the circus focusing on TV performances. He began swallowing swords at the age of 21.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bradbyers.com/bio.html|title=Brad Byers biography|publisher=www.bradbyers.com|accessdate=February 16, 2014}}</ref> Throughout his career he performed in more than 20 countries.<ref name=inland360/> He is listed in the 1999, 2000 and 2003 editions of the ''[[Guinness World Records|Guinness Book of Records]]''.<ref name=wr/> He also took part in [[America's Got Talent (season 4)|fourth]] and [[America's Got Talent (season 8)|eighth seasons]] of the [[NBC]]'s ''[[America's Got Talent]]'' TV-show (2009, 2013).
== Performances ==
=== Sword swallowing === He earned a Guinness World Record for "The Most Swords Swallowed and Twisted at One Time" by swallowing ten 27-inch swords one at a time until all 10 were in his esophagus and then twisting all 10 swords 180 degrees in his throat before withdrawing them and taking a bow.<ref name=wr>{{cite web|url=http://www.bradbyers.com/world_records.html|title=Guinness World Record|publisher=www.bradbyers.com|accessdate=February 16, 2014}}</ref> He is also among the few people in the World able to swallow a curved sword.
=== “Human toolbox” === “Human toolbox” is a moniker given to him by the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' for his activities involving inserting various [[tool]]s in his [[nasal cavity]].<ref name=inland360>{{cite web|url=http://inland360.com/pullman-sideshow-artist-brad-byers-on-nbcs-americas-got-talent-tonight/|title=Pullman sideshow artist Brad Byers on NBC’s "America’s Got Talent" tonight|publisher=inland360.com|first=Jennifer|last=Bauer|date=July 17, 2013|accessdate=February 16, 2014}}</ref> He hammers in a nail or an awl and hangs a weight on it. Seen through the X-ray, the nail stops in several millimeters from his brain. He puts in a fishing hook into his nasal cavity so that it shows up out of his mouth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacafe.com/watch/yt-_FwNj2A4FEU/americas_got_talent_most_dangerous_act_brad_byers_hook_and_drill/|title=America's Got Talent MOST DANGEROUS ACT: Brad Byers Hook and Drill|publisher=[[Metacafe]]|date=September 26, 2009|accessdate=February 16, 2014}}</ref> He also puts in a [[drill]] when it is being turned on. As it reaches maximum safe depth, he turns the drill off and on again when getting it out.<ref name=wr/>
=== Other === He laid on a bed of nails when his brother runs over him driving a [[quad bike]].<ref name=agt/>
