{{notability|date=April 2018}} [[File:Crystal Theatre - Dec 2012.JPG|thumb|]] '''Crystal Theatre''' is a historic theater in [[Gonzales, Texas]]. It has hosted [[vaudeville]] performances, [[silent movies]], and [[talkies]], and later became a coffee house and dinner theater venue. It was reopened in 2009 with a focus on youth programs.
==History== The theater opened in 1913<ref name=home>{{cite web|url=http://www.gonzalescrystaltheatre.org/about.html|title=About|publisher=Crystal Theatre |accessdate=May 30, 2018 }}</ref>{{primary source-inline|date=May 2018}} or 1917.<ref name=cinematreasures>{{cite web |author=Bryan Krefft |url=http://cinematreasures.org/theaters/17635 |title=Crystal Theatre |website=Cinema Treasures |accessdate=May 30, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Sonny Long |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=861&dat=20081031&id=SJE_AAAAIBAJ&sjid=zFUMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3945,5008 |title='The Glass Menagerie' on Tap in Gonzales |newspaper=The Victoria Advocate |date=October 31, 2008 |page=M12 }}</ref> With 586 seats, it was used for vaudeville, also under the name New Playhouse, and as a movie theater, then for dinner theater. It was restored in 1982 by Crystal Theatre, Inc. but was used only occasionally for a number of years<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gonzalesinquirer.com/stories/rising-from-the-ashes,17506? |title=Rising from the ashes |newspaper=The Gonzales Inquirer |date=January 7, 2007 }}</ref> before reopening in 2009 with a reduced seating capacity of 125<ref name=cinematreasures/> and a focus on youth programs.<ref name=home/> An acting program for high school students has taken place since the early 1990s<ref>{{cite news |author=Erik McCowan |url=http://www.gonzalesinquirer.com/stories/theatre-season-returns,1417? |title=Theatre season returns |newspaper=The Gonzales Inquirer |date=June 14, 2016 }}</ref> and now includes "Shakespeare ninjas".<ref name=home/><ref>{{cite news |author=Erik McCowan |url=http://www.gonzalesinquirer.com/stories/the-ninjas-are-back,2951? |title=The Ninjas are Back |newspaper=The Gonzales Inquirer |date=April 28, 2015 }}</ref> Barbara Crozier is the theatre's president.<ref>{{cite news |author=Erik McCowan |url=http://www.gonzalesinquirer.com/stories/council-gives-crystal-clarity-lets-the-grass-grow,1385? |title=Council gives Crystal clarity, lets the grass grow |newspaper=The Gonzales Inquirer |date=June 10, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Barbara Priesmeyer Crozier |url=http://www.gonzalesinquirer.com/stories/crystal-clear-excitement,14593? |title='Crystal Clear'&nbsp;...Excitement |newspaper=The Gonzales Inquirer |date=October 8, 2008 }}</ref>
