{{Infobox newspaper | name = Karjalan Sanomat | language = Finnish | foundation = 1920 | website = {{URL|http://www.karjalansanomat.ru/}} | headquarters = [[Petrozavodsk]] }}
'''''Karjalan Sanomat''''' (''Karelian News'') is a [[Finnish language]] newspaper from the [[Republic of Karelia]], published in [[Petrozavodsk]].
Previous names: * 1920-1923: Karjalan kommuuni (''Carelian Commune'') * 1923-1937: Punainen Karjala (''Red Carelia'') * 1938-1940: Советской Карелия (''Soviet Carelia'')<ref>{{cite book|author=Jukka Pietiläinen|title=From Participating to Informing. The Transition of Journalism in Russian Regional Press|date=2005|publisher=Nordicom|url=http://people.uta.fi/~tijupie/news%20paradigm%20russia.pdf|accessdate=18 December 2014|chapter=Diffusion of the News Paradigm 1850-2000}}</ref> * 1940-1955: Totuus (''Truth'') * 1955-1957: Leninilainen totuus (''Lenin's Truth'') * 1957-1991: Neuvosto-Karjala (''Soviet Carelia'') * 1991-: Karjalan sanomat (''Carelian News'')
From 1938 to 1940 the newspaper was printed in [[Karelian language|Karelian]] using [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic]], rather than Finnish.
